%% Workflow 1: User Accesses Dashboard to Create Notebook
sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Browser as Web Browser
    participant Route as OpenShift Route
    participant Proxy as kube-rbac-proxy
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard Backend
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API
    participant Webhook as Notebook Webhook
    participant Controller as Notebook Controller
    participant OAuth as OpenShift OAuth
    participant Notebook as Notebook Pod

    Note over User,Notebook: Workflow 1: User Creates Notebook via Dashboard

    User->>Browser: Navigate to dashboard URL
    Browser->>Route: HTTPS request<br/>(TLS 1.2+)
    Route->>Proxy: Forward to dashboard service<br/>(Port 8443)
    Proxy->>OAuth: Validate user session<br/>(OAuth 2.0)
    OAuth-->>Proxy: User authenticated
    Proxy->>Dashboard: Forward with user headers<br/>(X-Forwarded-User, etc.)
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Get user namespaces<br/>(SubjectAccessReview)
    K8sAPI-->>Dashboard: Namespace list
    Dashboard-->>Browser: Dashboard UI rendered<br/>(React SPA)

    Note over User: User creates notebook via UI

    Browser->>Dashboard: POST /api/notebooks<br/>(Bearer Token)
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Create Notebook CR<br/>(ServiceAccount token)
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validate Notebook CR<br/>(HTTPS webhook call)
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation successful
    K8sAPI-->>Dashboard: Notebook CR created
    Dashboard-->>Browser: Success response

    Note over Controller: Notebook Controller reconciles new Notebook CR

    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch Notebook CR<br/>(list-watch)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create StatefulSet<br/>(notebook container)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Service<br/>(notebook service)
    Controller->>OAuth: Create OAuth client<br/>(for notebook auth)
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Route<br/>(external access)
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Resources created

    User->>Browser: Click notebook URL
    Browser->>Route: HTTPS request to notebook route
    Route->>Notebook: Forward to OAuth Proxy sidecar
    Notebook->>OAuth: Validate user token
    OAuth-->>Notebook: User authorized
    Notebook-->>Browser: Jupyter UI

---

%% Workflow 2: Data Scientist Tracks Experiment in MLflow from Notebook
sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Notebook as Notebook Pod
    participant SDK as MLflow SDK
    participant Gateway as Istio Gateway
    participant MLflow as MLflow Server
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API
    participant PostgreSQL as PostgreSQL
    participant S3 as S3 Storage

    Note over User,S3: Workflow 2: ML Experiment Tracking with MLflow

    User->>Notebook: Run training script<br/>(mlflow.start_run())
    Notebook->>SDK: Initialize MLflow client<br/>(tracking_uri set)
    SDK->>Gateway: POST /api/2.0/mlflow/experiments/create<br/>(HTTPS, TLS 1.2+)
    Gateway->>MLflow: Forward request<br/>(optional mTLS)
    MLflow->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(validate user permissions)
    K8sAPI-->>MLflow: User authorized for experiments
    MLflow->>PostgreSQL: INSERT experiment metadata<br/>(TLS optional)
    PostgreSQL-->>MLflow: Experiment created
    MLflow-->>Gateway: Experiment ID
    Gateway-->>SDK: Response
    SDK-->>Notebook: Experiment context

    Note over User: Model training in progress

    Notebook->>SDK: Log metrics<br/>(mlflow.log_metric())
    SDK->>MLflow: POST /api/2.0/mlflow/runs/log-metric<br/>(Bearer Token)
    MLflow->>K8sAPI: Validate permissions
    MLflow->>PostgreSQL: INSERT metric data
    PostgreSQL-->>MLflow: Success

    Notebook->>SDK: Log model artifact<br/>(mlflow.log_artifact())
    SDK->>MLflow: POST /api/2.0/mlflow/runs/log-artifact
    MLflow->>S3: PUT /bucket/experiment-id/artifacts/<br/>(HTTPS, AWS IAM auth)
    S3-->>MLflow: Upload complete
    MLflow->>PostgreSQL: UPDATE artifact URI
    MLflow-->>SDK: Success
    SDK-->>Notebook: Artifacts logged

    User->>Browser: Open MLflow UI
    Browser->>Gateway: GET / (HTTPS)
    Gateway->>MLflow: Forward request
    MLflow->>PostgreSQL: SELECT experiments, runs, metrics
    PostgreSQL-->>MLflow: Query results
    MLflow-->>Browser: React UI with experiment data

---

%% Workflow 3: Feature Engineering with Feast
sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Notebook as Notebook Pod
    participant ConfigMap as Feast ConfigMap
    participant FeastSDK as Feast Python SDK
    participant Registry as Feast Registry Service
    participant Offline as Feast Offline Store<br/>(BigQuery)
    participant Online as Feast Online Store<br/>(Redis)
    participant Training as Training Job
    participant Serving as Model Serving

    Note over User,Serving: Workflow 3: Feature Store Lifecycle

    Note over Notebook: Notebook Controller injects Feast config at startup

    Notebook->>ConfigMap: Read Feast connection config<br/>(mounted as volume)
    User->>Notebook: Define feature views<br/>(Feast Python SDK)
    Notebook->>FeastSDK: Apply feature definitions<br/>(feast apply)
    FeastSDK->>Registry: Register feature views<br/>(gRPC/6570 or HTTP/6572)
    Registry->>S3: Store registry.db<br/>(S3/GCS backend)
    Registry-->>FeastSDK: Features registered

    Note over User: Push historical features for training

    Notebook->>FeastSDK: Push features to offline store<br/>(feast push)
    FeastSDK->>Offline: Write historical features<br/>(BigQuery API, HTTPS/443)
    Offline-->>FeastSDK: Features stored

    Note over Training: Training job retrieves historical features

    Training->>FeastSDK: Get historical features<br/>(get_historical_features())
    FeastSDK->>Offline: Query feature data<br/>(SQL query to BigQuery)
    Offline-->>FeastSDK: Feature dataset
    FeastSDK-->>Training: Training dataset with features

    Note over User: Materialize features to online store for serving

    Notebook->>FeastSDK: Materialize features<br/>(feast materialize)
    FeastSDK->>Offline: Read historical features<br/>(BigQuery SELECT)
    Offline-->>FeastSDK: Feature values
    FeastSDK->>Online: Write to online store<br/>(Redis MSET, TLS optional)
    Online-->>FeastSDK: Materialization complete

    Note over Serving: Model serving retrieves online features for inference

    Serving->>FeastSDK: Get online features<br/>(get_online_features())
    FeastSDK->>Online: Read from Redis<br/>(Redis GET commands)
    Online-->>FeastSDK: Feature values
    FeastSDK-->>Serving: Real-time features for inference

