%% Workflow 4: Platform Operator Installs Components
sequenceDiagram
    participant Admin as Platform Admin
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API
    participant Webhook as ODH Operator Webhook
    participant ODHOp as ODH Operator
    participant Renderer as Manifest Renderer
    participant OLM as OLM
    participant Quay as Quay.io Registry
    participant ComponentOp as Component Operators<br/>(Feast, MLflow)

    Note over Admin,ComponentOp: Workflow 4: Platform Installation via DataScienceCluster

    Admin->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply -f datasciencecluster.yaml
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validate DataScienceCluster CR<br/>(HTTPS webhook)
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validation successful
    K8sAPI-->>Admin: CR created
    K8sAPI->>ODHOp: Reconcile event<br/>(CR watch notification)

    ODHOp->>ODHOp: Read component configurations<br/>(Dashboard, Notebooks, MLflow, Feast enabled)
    ODHOp->>Renderer: Render component manifests<br/>(Kustomize/Helm processing)
    Renderer-->>ODHOp: Rendered YAML

    Note over ODHOp: Deploy Dashboard and Notebook Controller directly

    ODHOp->>K8sAPI: Create Dashboard Deployment<br/>(opendatahub namespace)
    ODHOp->>K8sAPI: Create Notebook Controller Deployment<br/>(redhat-ods-applications)
    K8sAPI-->>ODHOp: Resources created

    Note over ODHOp: Install component operators via OLM

    ODHOp->>K8sAPI: Create Subscription CR<br/>(for Feast Operator)
    ODHOp->>K8sAPI: Create Subscription CR<br/>(for MLflow Operator)
    K8sAPI->>OLM: Process Subscriptions
    OLM->>Quay: Pull operator images<br/>(HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+)
    Quay-->>OLM: Operator images
    OLM->>K8sAPI: Create Operator Deployments
    K8sAPI->>ComponentOp: Operators running

    Note over ComponentOp: Component operators deploy services

    ComponentOp->>K8sAPI: Create component resources<br/>(FeatureStore, MLflowConfig CRs)
    K8sAPI-->>ComponentOp: Services deployed

    ODHOp->>K8sAPI: Update DataScienceCluster status<br/>(all components ready)
    K8sAPI-->>Admin: kubectl get dsc<br/>(STATUS: Ready)
